45/*
46 * adapted from public domain strtok_r() by Charlie Gordon
47 *
48 * from comp.lang.c 9/14/2007
49 *
50 * http://groups.google.com/group/comp.lang.c/msg/2ab1ecbb86646684
51 *
52 * (Declaration that it's public domain):
53 * http://groups.google.com/group/comp.lang.c/msg/7c7b39328fefab9c
54 */
55
56#undef strtok_r
57static char* strtok_r(char* str, const char* delim, char** nextp)
58{
59 if (!str)
60 str = *nextp;
61
62 str += strspn(str, delim);
63
64 if (!*str)
65 return NULL;
66
67 char *ret = str;
68
69 str += strcspn(str, delim);
70
71 if (*str)
72 *str++ = '\0';
73
74 *nextp = str;
75
76 return ret;
77}

79#endif // if !defined(HAVE_STRTOK_R)

94x265_param *x265_param_alloc()
95{
96 x265_param* param = (x265_param*)x265_malloc(sizeof(x265_param));
97#ifdef SVT_HEVC
98 param->svtHevcParam = (EB_H265_ENC_CONFIGURATION*)x265_malloc(sizeof(EB_H265_ENC_CONFIGURATION));
99#endif
100 return param;
101}

103void x265_param_free(x265_param* p)
104{
105 x265_zone_free(p);
106#ifdef SVT_HEVC
107 x265_free(p->svtHevcParam);
108#endif
109 x265_free(p);
110}

385int x265_param_default_preset(x265_param* param, const char* preset, const char* tune)
386{
387#if EXPORT_C_API
388 ::x265_param_default(param);
389#else
390 X265_NS::x265_param_default(param);
391#endif
392
393 if (preset)
394 {
395 char *end;
396 int i = strtol(preset, &end, 10);
397 if (*end == 0 && i >= 0 && i < (int)(sizeof(x265_preset_names) / sizeof(*x265_preset_names) - 1))
398 preset = x265_preset_names[i];
399
400 if (!strcmp(preset, "ultrafast"))
401 {
402 param->maxNumMergeCand = 2;
403 param->bIntraInBFrames = 0;
404 param->lookaheadDepth = 5;
405 param->scenecutThreshold = 0; // disable lookahead
406 param->maxCUSize = 32;
407 param->minCUSize = 16;
408 param->bframes = 3;
409 param->bFrameAdaptive = 0;
410 param->subpelRefine = 0;
411 param->searchMethod = X265_DIA_SEARCH;
412 param->bEnableSAO = 0;
413 param->bEnableSignHiding = 0;
414 param->bEnableWeightedPred = 0;
415 param->rdLevel = 2;
416 param->maxNumReferences = 1;
417 param->limitReferences = 0;
418 param->rc.aqStrength = 0.0;
419 param->rc.aqMode = X265_AQ_NONE;
420 param->rc.hevcAq = 0;
421 param->rc.qgSize = 32;
422 param->bEnableFastIntra = 1;
423 }
424 else if (!strcmp(preset, "superfast"))
425 {
426 param->maxNumMergeCand = 2;
427 param->bIntraInBFrames = 0;
428 param->lookaheadDepth = 10;
429 param->maxCUSize = 32;
430 param->bframes = 3;
431 param->bFrameAdaptive = 0;
432 param->subpelRefine = 1;
433 param->bEnableWeightedPred = 0;
434 param->rdLevel = 2;
435 param->maxNumReferences = 1;
436 param->limitReferences = 0;
437 param->rc.aqStrength = 0.0;
438 param->rc.aqMode = X265_AQ_NONE;
439 param->rc.hevcAq = 0;
440 param->rc.qgSize = 32;
441 param->bEnableSAO = 0;
442 param->bEnableFastIntra = 1;
443 }
444 else if (!strcmp(preset, "veryfast"))
445 {
446 param->maxNumMergeCand = 2;
447 param->limitReferences = 3;
448 param->bIntraInBFrames = 0;
449 param->lookaheadDepth = 15;
450 param->bFrameAdaptive = 0;
451 param->subpelRefine = 1;
452 param->rdLevel = 2;
453 param->maxNumReferences = 2;
454 param->rc.qgSize = 32;
455 param->bEnableFastIntra = 1;
456 }
457 else if (!strcmp(preset, "faster"))
458 {
459 param->maxNumMergeCand = 2;
460 param->limitReferences = 3;
461 param->bIntraInBFrames = 0;
462 param->lookaheadDepth = 15;
463 param->bFrameAdaptive = 0;
464 param->rdLevel = 2;
465 param->maxNumReferences = 2;
466 param->bEnableFastIntra = 1;
467 }
468 else if (!strcmp(preset, "fast"))
469 {
470 param->maxNumMergeCand = 2;
471 param->limitReferences = 3;
472 param->bEnableEarlySkip = 0;
473 param->bIntraInBFrames = 0;
474 param->lookaheadDepth = 15;
475 param->bFrameAdaptive = 0;
476 param->rdLevel = 2;
477 param->maxNumReferences = 3;
478 param->bEnableFastIntra = 1;
479 }
480 else if (!strcmp(preset, "medium"))
481 {
482 /* defaults */
483 }
484 else if (!strcmp(preset, "slow"))
485 {
486 param->limitReferences = 3;
487 param->bEnableEarlySkip = 0;
488 param->bIntraInBFrames = 0;
489 param->bEnableRectInter = 1;
490 param->lookaheadDepth = 25;
491 param->rdLevel = 4;
492 param->rdoqLevel = 2;
493 param->psyRdoq = 1.0;
494 param->subpelRefine = 3;
495 param->searchMethod = X265_STAR_SEARCH;
496 param->maxNumReferences = 4;
497 param->limitModes = 1;
498 param->lookaheadSlices = 4; // limit parallelism as already enough work exists
499 }
500 else if (!strcmp(preset, "slower"))
501 {
502 param->bEnableEarlySkip = 0;
503 param->bEnableWeightedBiPred = 1;
504 param->bEnableAMP = 1;
505 param->bEnableRectInter = 1;
506 param->lookaheadDepth = 40;
507 param->bframes = 8;
508 param->tuQTMaxInterDepth = 3;
509 param->tuQTMaxIntraDepth = 3;
510 param->rdLevel = 6;
511 param->rdoqLevel = 2;
512 param->psyRdoq = 1.0;
513 param->subpelRefine = 4;
514 param->maxNumMergeCand = 4;
515 param->searchMethod = X265_STAR_SEARCH;
516 param->maxNumReferences = 5;
517 param->limitModes = 1;
518 param->lookaheadSlices = 0; // disabled for best quality
519 param->limitTU = 4;
520 }
521 else if (!strcmp(preset, "veryslow"))
522 {
523 param->bEnableEarlySkip = 0;
524 param->bEnableWeightedBiPred = 1;
525 param->bEnableAMP = 1;
526 param->bEnableRectInter = 1;
527 param->lookaheadDepth = 40;
528 param->bframes = 8;
529 param->tuQTMaxInterDepth = 3;
530 param->tuQTMaxIntraDepth = 3;
531 param->rdLevel = 6;
532 param->rdoqLevel = 2;
533 param->psyRdoq = 1.0;
534 param->subpelRefine = 4;
535 param->maxNumMergeCand = 5;
536 param->searchMethod = X265_STAR_SEARCH;
537 param->maxNumReferences = 5;
538 param->limitReferences = 0;
539 param->limitModes = 0;
540 param->lookaheadSlices = 0; // disabled for best quality
541 param->limitTU = 0;
542 }
543 else if (!strcmp(preset, "placebo"))
544 {
545 param->bEnableEarlySkip = 0;
546 param->bEnableWeightedBiPred = 1;
547 param->bEnableAMP = 1;
548 param->bEnableRectInter = 1;
549 param->lookaheadDepth = 60;
550 param->searchRange = 92;
551 param->bframes = 8;
552 param->tuQTMaxInterDepth = 4;
553 param->tuQTMaxIntraDepth = 4;
554 param->rdLevel = 6;
555 param->rdoqLevel = 2;
556 param->psyRdoq = 1.0;
557 param->subpelRefine = 5;
558 param->maxNumMergeCand = 5;
559 param->searchMethod = X265_STAR_SEARCH;
560 param->bEnableTransformSkip = 1;
561 param->recursionSkipMode = 0;
562 param->maxNumReferences = 5;
563 param->limitReferences = 0;
564 param->lookaheadSlices = 0; // disabled for best quality
565 // TODO: optimized esa
566 }
567 else
568 return -1;
569 }
570 if (tune)
571 {
572 if (!strcmp(tune, "psnr"))
573 {
574 param->rc.aqStrength = 0.0;
575 param->psyRd = 0.0;
576 param->psyRdoq = 0.0;
577 }
578 else if (!strcmp(tune, "ssim"))
579 {
580 param->rc.aqMode = X265_AQ_AUTO_VARIANCE;
581 param->psyRd = 0.0;
582 param->psyRdoq = 0.0;
583 }
584 else if (!strcmp(tune, "fastdecode") ||
585 !strcmp(tune, "fast-decode"))
586 {
587 param->bEnableLoopFilter = 0;
588 param->bEnableSAO = 0;
589 param->bEnableWeightedPred = 0;
590 param->bEnableWeightedBiPred = 0;
591 param->bIntraInBFrames = 0;
592 }
593 else if (!strcmp(tune, "zerolatency") ||
594 !strcmp(tune, "zero-latency"))
595 {
596 param->bFrameAdaptive = 0;
597 param->bframes = 0;
598 param->lookaheadDepth = 0;
599 param->scenecutThreshold = 0;
600 param->bHistBasedSceneCut = 0;
601 param->rc.cuTree = 0;
602 param->frameNumThreads = 1;
603 }
604 else if (!strcmp(tune, "grain"))
605 {
606 param->rc.ipFactor = 1.1;
607 param->rc.pbFactor = 1.0;
608 param->rc.cuTree = 0;
609 param->rc.aqMode = 0;
610 param->rc.hevcAq = 0;
611 param->rc.qpStep = 1;
612 param->rc.bEnableGrain = 1;
613 param->recursionSkipMode = 0;
614 param->psyRd = 4.0;
615 param->psyRdoq = 10.0;
616 param->bEnableSAO = 0;
617 param->rc.bEnableConstVbv = 1;
618 }
619 else if (!strcmp(tune, "animation"))
620 {
621 param->bframes = (param->bframes + 2) >= param->lookaheadDepth? param->bframes : param->bframes + 2;
622 param->psyRd = 0.4;
623 param->rc.aqStrength = 0.4;
624 param->deblockingFilterBetaOffset = 1;
625 param->deblockingFilterTCOffset = 1;
626 }
627 else if (!strcmp(tune, "vmaf")) /*Adding vmaf for x265 + SVT-HEVC integration support*/
628 {
629 /*vmaf is under development, currently x265 won't support vmaf*/
630 }
631 else
632 return -1;
633 }
634
635#ifdef SVT_HEVC
636 if (svt_set_preset(param, preset))
637 return -1;
638#endif
639
640 return 0;
641}
642
643static int x265_atobool(const char* str, bool& bError)
644{
645 if (!strcmp(str, "1") ||
646 !strcmp(str, "true") ||
647 !strcmp(str, "yes"))
648 return 1;
649 if (!strcmp(str, "0") ||
650 !strcmp(str, "false") ||
651 !strcmp(str, "no"))
652 return 0;
653 bError = true;
654 return 0;
655}
656
657static int parseName(const char* arg, const char* const* names, bool& bError)
658{
659 for (int i = 0; names[i]; i++)
660 if (!strcmp(arg, names[i]))
661 return i;
662
663 return x265_atoi(arg, bError);
664}
665/* internal versions of string-to-int with additional error checking */
666#undef atoi
667#undef atof
668#define atoi(str) x265_atoi(str, bError)
669#define atof(str) x265_atof(str, bError)
670#define atobool(str) (x265_atobool(str, bError))
671
672int x265_zone_param_parse(x265_param* p, const char* name, const char* value)
673{
674 bool bError = false;
675 char nameBuf[64];
676
677 if (!name)
678 return X265_PARAM_BAD_NAME;
679
680 // skip -- prefix if provided
681 if (name[0] == '-' && name[1] == '-')
682 name += 2;
683
684 // s/_/-/g
685 if (strlen(name) + 1 < sizeof(nameBuf) && strchr(name, '_'))
686 {
687 char *c;
688 strcpy(nameBuf, name);
689 while ((c = strchr(nameBuf, '_')) != 0)
690 *c = '-';
691
692 name = nameBuf;
693 }
694
695 if (!strncmp(name, "no-", 3))
696 {
697 name += 3;
698 value = !value || x265_atobool(value, bError) ? "false" : "true";
699 }
700 else if (!strncmp(name, "no", 2))
701 {
702 name += 2;
703 value = !value || x265_atobool(value, bError) ? "false" : "true";
704 }
705 else if (!value)
706 value = "true";
707 else if (value[0] == '=')
708 value++;
709
710#define OPT(STR) else if (!strcmp(name, STR))
711#define OPT2(STR1, STR2) else if (!strcmp(name, STR1) || !strcmp(name, STR2))

723 OPT("amp") p->bEnableAMP = atobool(value);
724 OPT("max-merge") p->maxNumMergeCand = (uint32_t)atoi(value);
725 OPT("rd") p->rdLevel = atoi(value);
726 OPT("radl") p->radl = atoi(value);
727 OPT2("rdoq", "rdoq-level")
728 {

734 }

739 OPT("scaling-list") p->scalingLists = strdup(value);

743 p->rc.rateControlMode = X265_RC_CRF;

746 {

748 p->rc.rateControlMode = X265_RC_CQP;
749 }

751 {
752 p->rc.bitrate = atoi(value);
753 p->rc.rateControlMode = X265_RC_ABR;

767 OPT("dynamic-rd") p->dynamicRd = atof(value);
768 else
769 return X265_PARAM_BAD_NAME;
770
771#undef OPT
772#undef OPT2
773
774 return bError ? X265_PARAM_BAD_VALUE : 0;
775}

777#undef atobool
778#undef atoi
779#undef atof

781/* internal versions of string-to-int with additional error checking */
782#undef atoi
783#undef atof
784#define atoi(str) x265_atoi(str, bError)
785#define atof(str) x265_atof(str, bError)
786#define atobool(str) (bNameWasBool = true, x265_atobool(str, bError))
787
788int x265_param_parse(x265_param* p, const char* name, const char* value)
789{
790 bool bError = false;
791 bool bNameWasBool = false;
792 bool bValueWasNull = !value;
793 bool bExtraParams = false;
794 char nameBuf[64];
795 static int count;
796
797 if (!name)
798 return X265_PARAM_BAD_NAME;
799
800 count++;
801 // skip -- prefix if provided
802 if (name[0] == '-' && name[1] == '-')
803 name += 2;
804
805 // s/_/-/g
806 if (strlen(name) + 1 < sizeof(nameBuf) && strchr(name, '_'))
807 {
808 char *c;
809 strcpy(nameBuf, name);
810 while ((c = strchr(nameBuf, '_')) != 0)
811 *c = '-';
812
813 name = nameBuf;
814 }
815
816 if (!strncmp(name, "no-", 3))
817 {
818 name += 3;
819 value = !value || x265_atobool(value, bError) ? "false" : "true";
820 }
821 else if (!strncmp(name, "no", 2))
822 {
823 name += 2;
824 value = !value || x265_atobool(value, bError) ? "false" : "true";
825 }
826 else if (!value)
827 value = "true";
828 else if (value[0] == '=')
829 value++;
830
831#if defined(_MSC_VER)
832#pragma warning(disable: 4127) // conditional expression is constant
833#endif
834#define OPT(STR) else if (!strcmp(name, STR))
835#define OPT2(STR1, STR2) else if (!strcmp(name, STR1) || !strcmp(name, STR2))

837#ifdef SVT_HEVC
838 if (p->bEnableSvtHevc)
839 {
840 if(svt_param_parse(p, name, value))
841 {
842 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_ERROR, "Error while parsing params \n");
843 bError = true;
844 }
845 return bError ? X265_PARAM_BAD_VALUE : 0;

847#endif

852#if X265_ARCH_X86

857 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_WARNING, "AVX512 is not supported\n");
858 }
859 else
860 {
861 if (bValueWasNull)
862 p->cpuid = atobool(value);
863 else
864 p->cpuid = parseCpuName(value, bError, false);
865 }
866#else
867 if (bValueWasNull)
868 p->cpuid = atobool(value);
869 else

873 OPT("fps")

1472int x265_atoi(const char* str, bool& bError)
1473{
1474 char *end;
1475 int v = strtol(str, &end, 0);
1476
1477 if (end == str || *end != '\0')
1478 bError = true;

1480}

1482double x265_atof(const char* str, bool& bError)
1483{
1484 char *end;
1485 double v = strtod(str, &end);
1486

1488 bError = true;

1492/* cpu name can be:
1493 * auto || true - x265::cpu_detect()
1494 * false || no - disabled
1495 * integer bitmap value
1496 * comma separated list of SIMD names, eg: SSE4.1,XOP */
1497int parseCpuName(const char* value, bool& bError, bool bEnableavx512)
1498{
1499 if (!value)
1500 {
1501 bError = 1;
1502 return 0;
1503 }
1504 int cpu;
1505 if (isdigit(value[0]))
1506 cpu = x265_atoi(value, bError);
1507 else
1508 cpu = !strcmp(value, "auto") || x265_atobool(value, bError) ? X265_NS::cpu_detect(bEnableavx512) : 0;
1509
1510 if (bError)
1511 {
1512 char *buf = strdup(value);
1513 char *tok, *saveptr = NULL, *init;
1514 bError = 0;
1515 cpu = 0;
1516 for (init = buf; (tok = strtok_r(init, ",", &saveptr)); init = NULL)
1517 {
1518 int i;
1519 for (i = 0; X265_NS::cpu_names[i].flags && strcasecmp(tok, X265_NS::cpu_names[i].name); i++)
1520 {
1521 }
1522
1523 cpu |= X265_NS::cpu_names[i].flags;
1524 if (!X265_NS::cpu_names[i].flags)
1525 bError = 1;
1526 }
1527
1528 free(buf);
1529 if ((cpu & X265_CPU_SSSE3) && !(cpu & X265_CPU_SSE2_IS_SLOW))
1530 cpu |= X265_CPU_SSE2_IS_FAST;
1531 }
1532
1533 return cpu;
1534}

1555
1556void setParamAspectRatio(x265_param* p, int width, int height)
1557{
1558 p->vui.aspectRatioIdc = X265_EXTENDED_SAR;
1559 p->vui.sarWidth = width;
1560 p->vui.sarHeight = height;
1561 for (size_t i = 0; i < sizeof(fixedRatios) / sizeof(fixedRatios[0]); i++)
1562 {
1563 if (width == fixedRatios[i][0] && height == fixedRatios[i][1])
1564 {
1565 p->vui.aspectRatioIdc = (int)i + 1;
1566 return;
1567 }
1568 }
1569}
1570
1571void getParamAspectRatio(x265_param* p, int& width, int& height)
1572{
1573 if (!p->vui.aspectRatioIdc)
1574 width = height = 0;
1575 else if ((size_t)p->vui.aspectRatioIdc <= sizeof(fixedRatios) / sizeof(fixedRatios[0]))
1576 {
1577 width = fixedRatios[p->vui.aspectRatioIdc - 1][0];
1578 height = fixedRatios[p->vui.aspectRatioIdc - 1][1];
1579 }
1580 else if (p->vui.aspectRatioIdc == X265_EXTENDED_SAR)
1581 {
1582 width = p->vui.sarWidth;
1583 height = p->vui.sarHeight;
1584 }
1585 else
1586 width = height = 0;
1587}

1589static inline int _confirm(x265_param* param, bool bflag, const char* message)
1590{
1591 if (!bflag)
1592 return 0;
1593
1594 x265_log(param, X265_LOG_ERROR, "%s\n", message);
1595 return 1;
1596}

1598int x265_check_params(x265_param* param)
1599{
1600#define CHECK(expr, msg) check_failed |= _confirm(param, expr, msg)
1601 int check_failed = 0; /* abort if there is a fatal configuration problem */
1602 CHECK(param->uhdBluray == 1 && (X265_DEPTH != 10 || param->internalCsp != 1 || param->interlaceMode != 0),
1603 "uhd-bd: bit depth, chroma subsample, source picture type must be 10, 4:2:0, progressive");
1604 CHECK(param->maxCUSize != 64 && param->maxCUSize != 32 && param->maxCUSize != 16,
1605 "max cu size must be 16, 32, or 64");
1606 if (check_failed == 1)
1607 return check_failed;
1608
1609 uint32_t maxLog2CUSize = (uint32_t)g_log2Size[param->maxCUSize];
1610 uint32_t tuQTMaxLog2Size = X265_MIN(maxLog2CUSize, 5);
1611 uint32_t tuQTMinLog2Size = 2; //log2(4)
1612
1613 CHECK((param->maxSlices > 1) && !param->bEnableWavefront,
1614 "Multiple-Slices mode must be enable Wavefront Parallel Processing (--wpp)");
1615 CHECK(param->internalBitDepth != X265_DEPTH,
1616 "internalBitDepth must match compiled bit depth");
1617 CHECK(param->minCUSize != 32 && param->minCUSize != 16 && param->minCUSize != 8,
1618 "minimim CU size must be 8, 16 or 32");
1619 CHECK(param->minCUSize > param->maxCUSize,
1620 "min CU size must be less than or equal to max CU size");
1621 CHECK(param->rc.qp < -6 * (param->internalBitDepth - 8) || param->rc.qp > QP_MAX_SPEC,
1622 "QP exceeds supported range (-QpBDOffsety to 51)");
1623 CHECK(param->fpsNum == 0 || param->fpsDenom == 0,
1624 "Frame rate numerator and denominator must be specified");
1625 CHECK(param->interlaceMode < 0 || param->interlaceMode > 2,
1626 "Interlace mode must be 0 (progressive) 1 (top-field first) or 2 (bottom field first)");
1627 CHECK(param->searchMethod < 0 || param->searchMethod > X265_FULL_SEARCH,
1628 "Search method is not supported value (0:DIA 1:HEX 2:UMH 3:HM 4:SEA 5:FULL)");
1629 CHECK(param->searchRange < 0,
1630 "Search Range must be more than 0");
1631 CHECK(param->searchRange >= 32768,
1632 "Search Range must be less than 32768");
1633 CHECK(param->subpelRefine > X265_MAX_SUBPEL_LEVEL,
1634 "subme must be less than or equal to X265_MAX_SUBPEL_LEVEL (7)");
1635 CHECK(param->subpelRefine < 0,
1636 "subme must be greater than or equal to 0");
1637 CHECK(param->limitReferences > 3,
1638 "limitReferences must be 0, 1, 2 or 3");
1639 CHECK(param->limitModes > 1,
1640 "limitRectAmp must be 0, 1");
1641 CHECK(param->frameNumThreads < 0 || param->frameNumThreads > X265_MAX_FRAME_THREADS,
1642 "frameNumThreads (--frame-threads) must be [0 .. X265_MAX_FRAME_THREADS)");
1643 CHECK(param->cbQpOffset < -12, "Min. Chroma Cb QP Offset is -12");
1644 CHECK(param->cbQpOffset > 12, "Max. Chroma Cb QP Offset is 12");
1645 CHECK(param->crQpOffset < -12, "Min. Chroma Cr QP Offset is -12");
1646 CHECK(param->crQpOffset > 12, "Max. Chroma Cr QP Offset is 12");
1647
1648 CHECK(tuQTMaxLog2Size > maxLog2CUSize,
1649 "QuadtreeTULog2MaxSize must be log2(maxCUSize) or smaller.");
1650
1651 CHECK(param->tuQTMaxInterDepth < 1 || param->tuQTMaxInterDepth > 4,
1652 "QuadtreeTUMaxDepthInter must be greater than 0 and less than 5");
1653 CHECK(maxLog2CUSize < tuQTMinLog2Size + param->tuQTMaxInterDepth - 1,
1654 "QuadtreeTUMaxDepthInter must be less than or equal to the difference between log2(maxCUSize) and QuadtreeTULog2MinSize plus 1");
1655 CHECK(param->tuQTMaxIntraDepth < 1 || param->tuQTMaxIntraDepth > 4,
1656 "QuadtreeTUMaxDepthIntra must be greater 0 and less than 5");
1657 CHECK(maxLog2CUSize < tuQTMinLog2Size + param->tuQTMaxIntraDepth - 1,
1658 "QuadtreeTUMaxDepthInter must be less than or equal to the difference between log2(maxCUSize) and QuadtreeTULog2MinSize plus 1");
1659 CHECK((param->maxTUSize != 32 && param->maxTUSize != 16 && param->maxTUSize != 8 && param->maxTUSize != 4),
1660 "max TU size must be 4, 8, 16, or 32");
1661 CHECK(param->limitTU > 4, "Invalid limit-tu option, limit-TU must be between 0 and 4");

1663 CHECK(param->maxNumMergeCand > 5, "MaxNumMergeCand must be 5 or smaller.");

1918 }

1922void x265_param_apply_fastfirstpass(x265_param* param)
1923{
1924 /* Set faster options in case of turbo firstpass */
1925 if (param->rc.bStatWrite && !param->rc.bStatRead)
1926 {
1927 param->maxNumReferences = 1;
1928 param->maxNumMergeCand = 1;

1930 param->bEnableFastIntra = 1;
1931 param->bEnableAMP = 0;
1932 param->searchMethod = X265_DIA_SEARCH;

1934 param->bEnableEarlySkip = 1;

1936 }

1939static void appendtool(x265_param* param, char* buf, size_t size, const char* toolstr)
1940{
1941 static const int overhead = (int)strlen("x265 [info]: tools: ");
1942
1943 if (strlen(buf) + strlen(toolstr) + overhead >= size)
1944 {
1945 x265_log(param, X265_LOG_INFO, "tools:%s\n", buf);
1946 sprintf(buf, " %s", toolstr);
1947 }
1948 else
1949 {
1950 strcat(buf, " ");
1951 strcat(buf, toolstr);
1952 }
1953}

1955void x265_print_params(x265_param* param)
1956{
1957 if (param->logLevel < X265_LOG_INFO)
1958 return;
1959
1960 if (param->interlaceMode)
1961 x265_log(param, X265_LOG_INFO, "Interlaced field inputs : %s\n", x265_interlace_names[param->interlaceMode]);
1962
1963 x265_log(param, X265_LOG_INFO, "Coding QT: max CU size, min CU size : %d / %d\n", param->maxCUSize, param->minCUSize);
1964
1965 x265_log(param, X265_LOG_INFO, "Residual QT: max TU size, max depth : %d / %d inter / %d intra\n",

1971 else

1973 x265_motion_est_names[param->searchMethod], param->searchRange, param->subpelRefine, param->maxNumMergeCand);
1974
1975 if (param->scenecutThreshold && param->keyframeMax != INT_MAX)
1976 x265_log(param, X265_LOG_INFO, "Keyframe min / max / scenecut / bias : %d / %d / %d / %.2lf \n",

1978 else if (param->bHistBasedSceneCut && param->keyframeMax != INT_MAX)
1979 x265_log(param, X265_LOG_INFO, "Keyframe min / max / scenecut / edge threshold : %d / %d / %d / %.2lf\n",
1980 param->keyframeMin, param->keyframeMax, param->bHistBasedSceneCut, param->edgeTransitionThreshold);

1984 if (param->cbQpOffset || param->crQpOffset)

1987 if (param->rdPenalty)
1988 x265_log(param, X265_LOG_INFO, "Intra 32x32 TU penalty type : %d\n", param->rdPenalty);
1989
1990 x265_log(param, X265_LOG_INFO, "Lookahead / bframes / badapt : %d / %d / %d\n", param->lookaheadDepth, param->bframes, param->bFrameAdaptive);
1991 x265_log(param, X265_LOG_INFO, "b-pyramid / weightp / weightb : %d / %d / %d\n",

1994 param->maxNumReferences, (param->limitReferences & X265_REF_LIMIT_CU) ? "on" : "off",
1995 (param->limitReferences & X265_REF_LIMIT_DEPTH) ? "on" : "off");
1996
1997 if (param->rc.aqMode)
1998 x265_log(param, X265_LOG_INFO, "AQ: mode / str / qg-size / cu-tree : %d / %0.1f / %d / %d\n", param->rc.aqMode,
1999 param->rc.aqStrength, param->rc.qgSize, param->rc.cuTree);
2000
2001 if (param->bLossless)
2002 x265_log(param, X265_LOG_INFO, "Rate Control : Lossless\n");
2003 else switch (param->rc.rateControlMode)
2004 {
2005 case X265_RC_ABR:
2006 x265_log(param, X265_LOG_INFO, "Rate Control / qCompress : ABR-%d kbps / %0.2f\n", param->rc.bitrate, param->rc.qCompress); break;
2007 case X265_RC_CQP:

2009 case X265_RC_CRF:
2010 x265_log(param, X265_LOG_INFO, "Rate Control / qCompress : CRF-%0.1f / %0.2f\n", param->rc.rfConstant, param->rc.qCompress); break;
2011 }
2012
2013 if (param->rc.vbvBufferSize)
2014 {
2015 if (param->vbvBufferEnd)
2016 x265_log(param, X265_LOG_INFO, "VBV/HRD buffer / max-rate / init / end / fr-adj: %d / %d / %.3f / %.3f / %.3f\n",

2018 else
2019 x265_log(param, X265_LOG_INFO, "VBV/HRD buffer / max-rate / init : %d / %d / %.3f\n",
2020 param->rc.vbvBufferSize, param->rc.vbvMaxBitrate, param->rc.vbvBufferInit);
2021 }
2022
2023 char buf[80] = { 0 };
2024 char tmp[40];
2025#define TOOLOPT(FLAG, STR) if (FLAG) appendtool(param, buf, sizeof(buf), STR);
2026#define TOOLVAL(VAL, STR) if (VAL) { sprintf(tmp, STR, VAL); appendtool(param, buf, sizeof(buf), tmp); }
2027 TOOLOPT(param->bEnableRectInter, "rect");

2029 TOOLOPT(param->limitModes, "limit-modes");

2035 TOOLVAL(param->psyRdoq, "psy-rdoq=%.2lf");

2037 TOOLOPT(param->bEnableEarlySkip, "early-skip");

2052 TOOLOPT(param->bEnableFastIntra, "fast-intra");
2053 TOOLOPT(param->bEnableStrongIntraSmoothing, "strong-intra-smoothing");
2054 TOOLVAL(param->lookaheadSlices, "lslices=%d");
2055 TOOLVAL(param->lookaheadThreads, "lthreads=%d")
2056 TOOLVAL(param->bCTUInfo, "ctu-info=%d");
2057 if (param->bAnalysisType == AVC_INFO)

2090char *x265_param2string(x265_param* p, int padx, int pady)
2091{
2092 char *buf, *s;
2093 size_t bufSize = 4000 + p->rc.zoneCount * 64;
2094 if (p->numaPools)
2095 bufSize += strlen(p->numaPools);
2096 if (p->masteringDisplayColorVolume)
2097 bufSize += strlen(p->masteringDisplayColorVolume);
2098 if (p->videoSignalTypePreset)
2099 bufSize += strlen(p->videoSignalTypePreset);
2100
2101 buf = s = X265_MALLOC(char, bufSize);
2102 if (!buf)
2103 return NULL;
2104#define BOOL(param, cliopt) \
2105 s += sprintf(s, " %s", (param) ? cliopt : "no-" cliopt);
2106
2107 s += sprintf(s, "cpuid=%d", p->cpuid);
2108 s += sprintf(s, " frame-threads=%d", p->frameNumThreads);
2109 if (p->numaPools)
2110 s += sprintf(s, " numa-pools=%s", p->numaPools);
2111 BOOL(p->bEnableWavefront, "wpp");
2112 BOOL(p->bDistributeModeAnalysis, "pmode");
2113 BOOL(p->bDistributeMotionEstimation, "pme");
2114 BOOL(p->bEnablePsnr, "psnr");
2115 BOOL(p->bEnableSsim, "ssim");
2116 s += sprintf(s, " log-level=%d", p->logLevel);
2117 if (p->csvfn)
2118 s += sprintf(s, " csv csv-log-level=%d", p->csvLogLevel);
2119 s += sprintf(s, " bitdepth=%d", p->internalBitDepth);
2120 s += sprintf(s, " input-csp=%d", p->internalCsp);
2121 s += sprintf(s, " fps=%u/%u", p->fpsNum, p->fpsDenom);
2122 s += sprintf(s, " input-res=%dx%d", p->sourceWidth - padx, p->sourceHeight - pady);
2123 s += sprintf(s, " interlace=%d", p->interlaceMode);
2124 s += sprintf(s, " total-frames=%d", p->totalFrames);
2125 if (p->chunkStart)
2126 s += sprintf(s, " chunk-start=%d", p->chunkStart);
2127 if (p->chunkEnd)
2128 s += sprintf(s, " chunk-end=%d", p->chunkEnd);
2129 s += sprintf(s, " level-idc=%d", p->levelIdc);
2130 s += sprintf(s, " high-tier=%d", p->bHighTier);
2131 s += sprintf(s, " uhd-bd=%d", p->uhdBluray);
2132 s += sprintf(s, " ref=%d", p->maxNumReferences);
2133 BOOL(p->bAllowNonConformance, "allow-non-conformance");
2134 BOOL(p->bRepeatHeaders, "repeat-headers");

2348
2349bool parseLambdaFile(x265_param* param)
2350{
2351 if (!param->rc.lambdaFileName)
2352 return false;
2353
2354 FILE *lfn = x265_fopen(param->rc.lambdaFileName, "r");
2355 if (!lfn)
2356 {
2357 x265_log_file(param, X265_LOG_ERROR, "unable to read lambda file <%s>\n", param->rc.lambdaFileName);
2358 return true;
2359 }
2360
2361 char line[2048];
2362 char *toksave = NULL, *tok = NULL, *buf = NULL;
2363
2364 for (int t = 0; t < 3; t++)
2365 {
2366 double *table = t ? x265_lambda2_tab : x265_lambda_tab;
2367
2368 for (int i = 0; i < QP_MAX_MAX + 1; i++)
2369 {
2370 double value;
2371
2372 do
2373 {
2374 if (!tok)
2375 {
2376 /* consume a line of text file */
2377 if (!fgets(line, sizeof(line), lfn))
2378 {
2379 fclose(lfn);
2380
2381 if (t < 2)
2382 {
2383 x265_log(param, X265_LOG_ERROR, "lambda file is incomplete\n");
2384 return true;
2385 }
2386 else
2387 return false;
2388 }
2389
2390 /* truncate at first hash */
2391 char *hash = strchr(line, '#');
2392 if (hash) *hash = 0;
2393 buf = line;
2394 }
2395
2396 tok = strtok_r(buf, " ,", &toksave);
2397 buf = NULL;
2398 if (tok && sscanf(tok, "%lf", &value) == 1)
2399 break;
2400 }
2401 while (1);
2402
2403 if (t == 2)
2404 {
2405 x265_log(param, X265_LOG_ERROR, "lambda file contains too many values\n");
2406 fclose(lfn);
2407 return true;
2408 }
2409 else
2410 x265_log(param, X265_LOG_DEBUG, "lambda%c[%d] = %lf\n", t ? '2' : ' ', i, value);
2411 table[i] = value;
2412 }
2413 }
2414
2415 fclose(lfn);
2416 return false;
2417}

2831int svt_set_preset(x265_param* param, const char* preset)
2832{
2833 EB_H265_ENC_CONFIGURATION* svtHevcParam = (EB_H265_ENC_CONFIGURATION*)param->svtHevcParam;
2834
2835 if (preset)
2836 {
2837 if (!strcmp(preset, "ultrafast")) svtHevcParam->encMode = 11;
2838 else if (!strcmp(preset, "superfast")) svtHevcParam->encMode = 10;
2839 else if (!strcmp(preset, "veryfast")) svtHevcParam->encMode = 9;
2840 else if (!strcmp(preset, "faster")) svtHevcParam->encMode = 8;
2841 else if (!strcmp(preset, "fast")) svtHevcParam->encMode = 7;
2842 else if (!strcmp(preset, "medium")) svtHevcParam->encMode = 6;
2843 else if (!strcmp(preset, "slow")) svtHevcParam->encMode = 5;
2844 else if (!strcmp(preset, "slower")) svtHevcParam->encMode =4;
2845 else if (!strcmp(preset, "veryslow")) svtHevcParam->encMode = 3;
2846 else if (!strcmp(preset, "placebo")) svtHevcParam->encMode = 2;
2847 else return -1;
2848 }
2849 return 0;
2850}
2851
2852int svt_param_parse(x265_param* param, const char* name, const char* value)
2853{
2854 bool bError = false;
2855#define OPT(STR) else if (!strcmp(name, STR))
2856
2857 EB_H265_ENC_CONFIGURATION* svtHevcParam = (EB_H265_ENC_CONFIGURATION*)param->svtHevcParam;
2858 if (0);
2859 OPT("input-res") bError |= sscanf(value, "%dx%d", &svtHevcParam->sourceWidth, &svtHevcParam->sourceHeight) != 2;
2860 OPT("input-depth") svtHevcParam->encoderBitDepth = atoi(value);
2861 OPT("total-frames") svtHevcParam->framesToBeEncoded = atoi(value);
2862 OPT("frames") svtHevcParam->framesToBeEncoded = atoi(value);
2863 OPT("fps")
2864 {
2865 if (sscanf(value, "%u/%u", &svtHevcParam->frameRateNumerator, &svtHevcParam->frameRateDenominator) == 2)
2866 ;
2867 else
2868 {
2869 int fps = atoi(value);
2870 svtHevcParam->frameRateDenominator = 1;
2871
2872 if (fps < 1000)
2873 svtHevcParam->frameRate = fps << 16;
2874 else
2875 svtHevcParam->frameRate = fps;
2876 }
2877 }
2878 OPT2("level-idc", "level")
2879 {
2880 /* allow "5.1" or "51", both converted to integer 51 */
2881 /* if level-idc specifies an obviously wrong value in either float or int,
2882 throw error consistently. Stronger level checking will be done in encoder_open() */
2883 if (atof(value) < 10)
2884 svtHevcParam->level = (int)(10 * atof(value) + .5);
2885 else if (atoi(value) < 100)
2886 svtHevcParam->level = atoi(value);
2887 else
2888 bError = true;
2889 }
2890 OPT2("pools", "numa-pools")
2891 {
2892 char *pools = strdup(value);
2893 char *temp1, *temp2;
2894 int count = 0;
2895
2896 for (temp1 = strstr(pools, ","); temp1 != NULL; temp1 = strstr(temp2, ","))
2897 {
2898 temp2 = ++temp1;
2899 count++;
2900 }
2901
2902 if (count > 1)
2903 x265_log(param, X265_LOG_WARNING, "SVT-HEVC Encoder supports pools option only upto 2 sockets \n");
2904 else if (count == 1)
2905 {
2906 temp1 = strtok(pools, ",");
2907 temp2 = strtok(NULL, ",");
2908
2909 if (!strcmp(temp1, "+"))
2910 {
2911 if (!strcmp(temp2, "+")) svtHevcParam->targetSocket = -1;
2912 else if (!strcmp(temp2, "-")) svtHevcParam->targetSocket = 0;
2913 else svtHevcParam->targetSocket = -1;
2914 }
2915 else if (!strcmp(temp1, "-"))
2916 {
2917 if (!strcmp(temp2, "+")) svtHevcParam->targetSocket = 1;
2918 else if (!strcmp(temp2, "-")) x265_log(param, X265_LOG_ERROR, "Shouldn't exclude both sockets for pools option %s \n", pools);
2919 else if (!strcmp(temp2, "*")) svtHevcParam->targetSocket = 1;
2920 else
2921 {
2922 svtHevcParam->targetSocket = 1;
2923 svtHevcParam->logicalProcessors = atoi(temp2);
2924 }
2925 }
2926 else svtHevcParam->targetSocket = -1;
2927 }
2928 else
2929 {
2930 if (!strcmp(temp1, "*")) svtHevcParam->targetSocket = -1;
2931 else
2932 {
2933 svtHevcParam->targetSocket = 0;
2934 svtHevcParam->logicalProcessors = atoi(temp1);
2935 }
2936 }
2937 }
2938 OPT("high-tier") svtHevcParam->tier = x265_atobool(value, bError);
2939 OPT("qpmin") svtHevcParam->minQpAllowed = atoi(value);
2940 OPT("qpmax") svtHevcParam->maxQpAllowed = atoi(value);
2941 OPT("rc-lookahead") svtHevcParam->lookAheadDistance = atoi(value);
2942 OPT("scenecut")
2943 {
2944 svtHevcParam->sceneChangeDetection = x265_atobool(value, bError);
2945 if (bError || svtHevcParam->sceneChangeDetection)
2946 {
2947 bError = false;
2948 svtHevcParam->sceneChangeDetection = 1;
2949 }
2950 }
2951 OPT("open-gop")
2952 {
2953 if (x265_atobool(value, bError))
2954 svtHevcParam->intraRefreshType = 1;
2955 else
2956 svtHevcParam->intraRefreshType = 2;
2957 }
2958 OPT("deblock")
2959 {
2960 if (strtol(value, NULL, 0))
2961 svtHevcParam->disableDlfFlag = 0;
2962 else if (x265_atobool(value, bError) == 0 && !bError)
2963 svtHevcParam->disableDlfFlag = 1;
2964 }
2965 OPT("sao") svtHevcParam->enableSaoFlag = (uint8_t)x265_atobool(value, bError);
2966 OPT("keyint") svtHevcParam->intraPeriodLength = atoi(value);
2967 OPT2("constrained-intra", "cip") svtHevcParam->constrainedIntra = (uint8_t)x265_atobool(value, bError);
2968 OPT("vui-timing-info") svtHevcParam->videoUsabilityInfo = x265_atobool(value, bError);
2969 OPT("hdr") svtHevcParam->highDynamicRangeInput = x265_atobool(value, bError);
2970 OPT("aud") svtHevcParam->accessUnitDelimiter = x265_atobool(value, bError);
2971 OPT("qp")
2972 {
2973 svtHevcParam->rateControlMode = 0;
2974 svtHevcParam->qp = atoi(value);
2975 }
2976 OPT("bitrate")
2977 {
2978 svtHevcParam->rateControlMode = 1;
2979 svtHevcParam->targetBitRate = atoi(value);
2980 }
2981 OPT("interlace")
2982 {
2983 svtHevcParam->interlacedVideo = (uint8_t)x265_atobool(value, bError);
2984 if (bError || svtHevcParam->interlacedVideo)
2985 {
2986 bError = false;
2987 svtHevcParam->interlacedVideo = 1;
2988 }
2989 }
2990 OPT("svt-hme")
2991 {
2992 svtHevcParam->enableHmeFlag = (uint8_t)x265_atobool(value, bError);
2993 if (svtHevcParam->enableHmeFlag) svtHevcParam->useDefaultMeHme = 1;
2994 }
2995 OPT("svt-search-width") svtHevcParam->searchAreaWidth = atoi(value);
2996 OPT("svt-search-height") svtHevcParam->searchAreaHeight = atoi(value);
2997 OPT("svt-compressed-ten-bit-format") svtHevcParam->compressedTenBitFormat = x265_atobool(value, bError);
2998 OPT("svt-speed-control") svtHevcParam->speedControlFlag = x265_atobool(value, bError);
2999 OPT("svt-preset-tuner")
3000 {
3001 if (svtHevcParam->encMode == 2)
3002 {
3003 if (!strcmp(value, "0")) svtHevcParam->encMode = 0;
3004 else if (!strcmp(value, "1")) svtHevcParam->encMode = 1;
3005 else
3006 {
3007 x265_log(param, X265_LOG_ERROR, " Unsupported value=%s for svt-preset-tuner \n", value);
3008 bError = true;
3009 }
3010 }
3011 else
3012 x265_log(param, X265_LOG_WARNING, " svt-preset-tuner should be used only with ultrafast preset; Ignoring it \n");
3013 }
3014 OPT("svt-hierarchical-level") svtHevcParam->hierarchicalLevels = atoi(value);
3015 OPT("svt-base-layer-switch-mode") svtHevcParam->baseLayerSwitchMode = atoi(value);
3016 OPT("svt-pred-struct") svtHevcParam->predStructure = (uint8_t)atoi(value);
3017 OPT("svt-fps-in-vps") svtHevcParam->fpsInVps = (uint8_t)x265_atobool(value, bError);
3018 OPT("master-display") svtHevcParam->useMasteringDisplayColorVolume = (uint8_t)atoi(value);
3019 OPT("max-cll") bError |= sscanf(value, "%hu,%hu", &svtHevcParam->maxCLL, &svtHevcParam->maxFALL) != 2;
3020 OPT("nalu-file") svtHevcParam->useNaluFile = (uint8_t)atoi(value);
3021 OPT("dolby-vision-profile")
3022 {
3023 if (atof(value) < 10)
3024 svtHevcParam->dolbyVisionProfile = (int)(10 * atof(value) + .5);
3025 else if (atoi(value) < 100)
3026 svtHevcParam->dolbyVisionProfile = atoi(value);
3027 else
3028 bError = true;
3029 }
3030 OPT("hrd")
3031 svtHevcParam->hrdFlag = (uint32_t)x265_atobool(value, bError);
3032 OPT("vbv-maxrate")
